# egregore project workflow

Core rules: `make rules-link` → [core-karpathy-guidelines.mdc](core-karpathy-guidelines.mdc), [core-workflow-chain.mdc](core-workflow-chain.mdc), [core-parallel-branches.mdc](core-parallel-branches.mdc), [core-agent-critic.mdc](core-agent-critic.mdc), [core-agent-documentation.mdc](core-agent-documentation.mdc), [core-kaizen.mdc](core-kaizen.mdc).

Follow [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md).

## Architecture (do not break)

- Event-driven: `interfaces/ingress` → `EventRouter` → `WorkerOrchestrator` → `SecureAgentBus`.
- Product agents in `agents/personas/` only — no Python modules named after personas under `agents/`.
- LLM via `cys_core/llm` (LiteLLM); config via `bootstrap/settings.py`.
- Do not restore batch `assess` pipeline as primary path.
- Domain coverage gate: **100%** on `cys_core/domain`.

## Master plan & branches

- Master plan: [docs/MASTER_PLAN_SECURE_PLATFORM.md](../../docs/MASTER_PLAN_SECURE_PLATFORM.md)
- Branch prefix: `egregore/phase-<NN>-<slug>` from latest `main`
- Phase scope: sub-phase `P{x}.{y}.{z}` only; ≤5 files per PR

## Required before finishing

1. `./scripts/pytest_batches.sh` for touched code; domain changes need `tests/domain/` at 100%.
2. Security changes: `tests/adversarial/` when touching ingress, patterns, or tool policy.
3. Commit, push, update MASTER_PLAN / AGENTS if behavior changed.

## Git hygiene

- Never commit `.env`, API keys, `.agents/` build cache, or injection corpus payloads.
- Do not edit `.cursor/plans/` unless user explicitly requests.
